==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from the same stem as the foul-smelling carboxylic acid liberated in [[rancid]] [[butter]], ''[[butyric acid]]'' + ''[[-ane]]''.

===Noun===
'''butane'''

#{{Chemistry}} A [[hydrocarbon]] (either of the two [[isomer]]s of C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>10</sub> n-butane, and 2-methyl-propane) found in [[natural]] [[gas]].

